"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533551\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 04, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104wvf1665702876540.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wvf1665702876540.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wvf1665702876540.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"wvf1665702876540\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Settings for All Character Sets\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> and <span class=\"ph filepath\">.asn</span> settings are used for all character sets.\n </p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"wvf1665702876540__table_d2966e1_d2967e1_d2968e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Settings in <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"wvf1665702876540__table_d2966e1_d2967e1_d2968e1__entry__1\">\n Setting\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"wvf1665702876540__table_d2966e1_d2967e1_d2968e1__entry__2\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wvf1665702876540__table_d2966e1_d2967e1_d2968e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lvk1665702674531.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lvk1665702674531.html\" title=\"Enable the use of the Graphic data type for double-byte-only storage\">nls</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wvf1665702876540__table_d2966e1_d2967e1_d2968e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Specify the character set that is supported by the current Uniface installation.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wvf1665702876540__table_d2966e1_d2967e1_d2968e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jav1665702616964.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jav1665702616964.html\" title=\"Determines the prefix character used when displaying profile characters in widgets (but not Unifields).\">Profile</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wvf1665702876540__table_d2966e1_d2967e1_d2968e1__entry__2\">\n Specify the display profile characters in widgets. (Windows only)\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wvf1665702876540__table_d2966e1_d2967e1_d2968e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vas1665702670549.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vas1665702670549.html\" title=\"The [printer] section of the initialization file defines the fonts used for printing, and logical printer definitions.\">[printer]</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wyv1665702675417.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wyv1665702675417.html\" title=\"The [screen] section of the initialization file defines the fonts used in the GUI user interface and additional settings for screen display.\">[screen]</a>\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lvk1665702674531.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lvk1665702674531.html\" title=\"Enable the use of the Graphic data type for double-byte-only storage\">nls</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wvf1665702876540__table_d2966e1_d2967e1_d2968e1__entry__2\">Some GUI settings are dependent on the character\n                     set. For example, a Simplified Chinese Uniface version, has setting\n                           <p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">HyperLabel=Arial,Simplified Chinese,8,underline</code>\n</p></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wvf1665702876540__p_d28727e1_d28728e1_d28729e1\">Uniface is character set independent. It's internal character set is UTF-8, but it can be run in any Uniface supported character sets environment. Such independence is achieved by means of translation tables. A translation table defines a mapping between the Uniface internal character set and a Uniface supported character set. For example, the Euro sign € is coded as x20AC (Unicode) in Uniface internally, and as x80 in character set CP1252. In the Uniface translation table CP1252, there is an entry that maps x20AC to x80 and vice versa. When Uniface writes € into a file that is stored as CP1252 code, Uniface sends code x80 to the file.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"wvf1665702876540__table_d2969e1_d2970e1_d2971e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Translation Tables in Assignment File</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"wvf1665702876540__table_d2969e1_d2970e1_d2971e1__entry__1\">\n Setting\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"wvf1665702876540__table_d2969e1_d2970e1_d2971e1__entry__2\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wvf1665702876540__table_d2969e1_d2970e1_d2971e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"iyr1665702568737.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iyr1665702568737.html\" title=\"Set or return the value of $SYS_CHARSET, which defines the character set used to communicate with components that are not Unicode-based, for example C components.\">$sys_charset</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wvf1665702876540__table_d2969e1_d2970e1_d2971e1__entry__2\">\n Specify a character set used to communicate with the operating system.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wvf1665702876540__table_d2969e1_d2970e1_d2971e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fmh1665702657664.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fmh1665702657664.html\" title=\"Set or return the value of $DEF_CHARSET, which defines the character set used for storing data in String fields with C packing code.\">$def_charset</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wvf1665702876540__table_d2969e1_d2970e1_d2971e1__entry__2\">\n Specify a character set used to communicate with the database.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wvf1665702876540__table_d2969e1_d2970e1_d2971e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zbn1665702665252.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zbn1665702665252.html\" title=\"Return or set the current keyboard translation table.\">$keyboard</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wvf1665702876540__table_d2969e1_d2970e1_d2971e1__entry__2\">\n Specify a translation table used for entering characters.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wvf1665702876540__table_d2969e1_d2970e1_d2971e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"oma1720015839839.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oma1720015839839.html\" title=\"Presents the form on the screen as display-only.\">display</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wvf1665702876540__table_d2969e1_d2970e1_d2971e1__entry__2\">\n Specify a translation table used for displaying characters.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wvf1665702876540__section_mb1_brb_rcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d820388e261\">$LANGUAGE</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wvf1665702876540__p_d28733e1_d28734e1_d28735e1\">Uniface installation program initializes the\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$LANGUAGE</span> with the language abbreviation of the installed\n            character set in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.asn</span> file. For example, if you selected\n            Japanese during the installation, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$LANGUAGE</span> = <code class=\"ph codeph\">JPN</code>.\n            However, you can change this setting according to the library and global objects used in\n            your application. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ead1665702665322.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ead1665702665322.html\" title=\"Specify the language used by the Sybase SQL Server for error messages.\">language</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wvf1665702876540__p_d28736e1_d28737e1_d28738e1\">You can define multiple language versions of global\n            objects in a library. <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$LANGUAGE</span> is used together with\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$VARIATION</span> to determine which language version of the global\n            objects are used in your application. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jpo1705564833726.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jpo1705564833726.html\" title=\"Runtime libraries contain objects that can be used by all components in the application. These objects can include global objects, such as messages, menus, and global variables, as well as translation tables and language setups.\">Libraries of Runtime Objects</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"exe1665702665391.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/exe1665702665391.html\" title=\"Return or specify the name of the library containing objects needed by the application or component.\">$variation</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wvf1665702876540__section_lxb_3rb_rcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d820388e312\">[META_<var class=\"keyword varname\">LANGUAGE</var>] </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wvf1665702876540__p_d28742e1_d28743e1_d28744e1\">In earlier Uniface versions, its internal character\n            set was the meta character set. From version 9, Unicode becomes its internal character\n            set. For the compatibility reason, the meta character set is still used. These result in\n            some problems. This assignment section is used to define your own character mapping to\n            solve the problems. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vmy1665702874862.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vmy1665702874862.html\" title=\"Earlier versions of Uniface used the Uniface meta character set as its internal character set. Uniface 9 uses Unicode as its internal character set. For compatibility reasons, the meta character set is still used, but this results in some problems. Assignment settings are available to solve these issues.\">Unicode Compatibility Issues</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wvf1665702876540__section_ucn_prb_rcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d820388e332\">DEFAULTENCODING</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wvf1665702876540__p_d28748e1_d28749e1_d28750e1\">For a web application, the browser should be able to\n            display the specific language. Make sure that the browser's Encoding view is switched to\n            the correct language. To do so, set the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">DEFAULTENCODING</span> parameter.\n            For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sfg1665702742533.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sfg1665702742533.html\" title=\"Specifies the encoding used by the Web Application Server to convert inbound and outbound TEXT, HTML, and XML, if no encoding is specified in the request. This setting influences the conversion to the web browser.\">DEFAULTENCODING</a>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533551\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533551\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Settings for All Character Sets Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 04, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Settings for All Character Sets The .ini and .asn settings are used for all character sets. Table 1. Settings in .ini file Setting Description nls Specify the character set that is supported by the current Uniface installation. Profile Specify the display profile characters in widgets. (Windows only) [printer] and [screen] nls Some GUI settings are dependent on the character set. For example, a Simplified Chinese Uniface version, has setting HyperLabel=Arial,Simplified Chinese,8,underline Uniface is character set independent. It's internal character set is UTF-8, but it can be run in any Uniface supported character sets environment. Such independence is achieved by means of translation tables. A translation table defines a mapping between the Uniface internal character set and a Uniface supported character set. For example, the Euro sign € is coded as x20AC (Unicode) in Uniface internally, and as x80 in character set CP1252. In the Uniface translation table CP1252, there is an entry that maps x20AC to x80 and vice versa. When Uniface writes € into a file that is stored as CP1252 code, Uniface sends code x80 to the file. Table 2. Translation Tables in Assignment File Setting Description $sys_charset Specify a character set used to communicate with the operating system. $def_charset Specify a character set used to communicate with the database. $keyboard Specify a translation table used for entering characters. display Specify a translation table used for displaying characters. $LANGUAGE Uniface installation program initializes the $LANGUAGE with the language abbreviation of the installed character set in the usys.asn file. For example, if you selected Japanese during the installation, $LANGUAGE = JPN . However, you can change this setting according to the library and global objects used in your application. For more information, see language . You can define multiple language versions of global objects in a library. $LANGUAGE is used together with $VARIATION to determine which language version of the global objects are used in your application. For more information, see Libraries of Runtime Objects and $variation . [META_ LANGUAGE ] In earlier Uniface versions, its internal character set was the meta character set. From version 9, Unicode becomes its internal character set. For the compatibility reason, the meta character set is still used. These result in some problems. This assignment section is used to define your own character mapping to solve the problems. For more information, see Unicode Compatibility Issues . DEFAULTENCODING For a web application, the browser should be able to display the specific language. Make sure that the browser's Encoding view is switched to the correct language. To do so, set the DEFAULTENCODING parameter. For more information, see DEFAULTENCODING . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}